{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":556339,"duration_api_ms":514395,"num_turns":74,"result":"```json\n{\n  \"change_summary\": \"Seventeenth remediation round addressing 5 amendments (4 implemented, amendment 1 and 4 merged as same issue): (1+4) Reverted the pre-backoff snapshot write from bare `?` back to best-effort with `tracing::warn!` on failure. A transient disk error during backoff should not abort the retry loop — that would be exactly the fragility this project is fixing. The warn log provides operator visibility. (2) Added 8 unit tests: 5 for classify_exit_failure (exit 127 → BinaryNotFound, exit 1 → TransportFailure, exit 0 → TransportFailure, signal 11/SIGSEGV → TransportFailure, signal 6/SIGABRT → TransportFailure) and 3 for derive_resume_state (retryable failure preserves attempt count at failed+1, no prior failures starts at attempt 1, completion round advance resets retry tracking). (3) Fixed cross-round retry budget bleed: retryable_failed_attempts map is now cleared on CompletionRoundAdvanced events and individual entries are removed on StageCompleted, so a stage that needed retries in round 1 starts fresh in round 2. (5) Fixed bare-command ENOENT misclassification when working directory is missing: added `request.working_dir.exists()` check before classifying as BinaryNotFound, so a vanished worktree directory produces TransportFailure (retryable) instead of terminal BinaryNotFound.\",\n  \"outstanding_risks\": [\n    \"Process group kill cannot be implemented due to #![forbid(unsafe_code)] — pre_exec(setsid) requires unsafe, and std::process::Command::process_group is nightly-only. Grandchildren spawned by claude/codex CLI may survive as orphans after the parent is killed on timeout/cancel.\",\n    \"The pre-backoff snapshot write is now best-effort: if it fails, the backoff proceeds but a crash during the sleep window leaves the project stranded in Running state (the pre-existing behavior before CR14). The tracing::warn provides operator visibility for diagnosis. This is a deliberate trade-off — aborting the retry loop on a transient disk error is worse than the small risk of stranding.\",\n    \"The working_dir.exists() check in the spawn error path has a TOCTOU window: the directory could disappear between the exists() check and the next retry attempt. This is benign — the retry will fail again and either the directory returns (transient issue) or retries exhaust normally.\",\n    \"The BinaryNotFound failure class name is used for both missing binaries and missing API keys. Doc comments clarify this dual use as a general 'fatal infrastructure prerequisite' signal.\",\n    \"The jitter implementation uses SystemTime subsec_nanos which is not cryptographically random, but provides sufficient dispersion for retry staggering.\"\n  ],\n  \"steps\": [\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Reverted pre-backoff snapshot write from bare `?` to best-effort `if let Err` with `tracing::warn!` at engine.rs:4643. A transient I/O error now logs a warning and allows the retry loop to continue instead of aborting. The comment explains the trade-off: worst case is the pre-existing behavior (stranded in Running on crash during backoff).\",\n      \"order\": 1,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Added `retryable_failed_attempts.remove(&(stage_id, current_cycle))` on StageCompleted events in derive_resume_state, so a successfully completed stage's retry history doesn't carry forward to future revisits of the same stage+cycle.\",\n      \"order\": 2,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Added `retryable_failed_attempts.clear()` on CompletionRoundAdvanced events in derive_resume_state. A new completion round means logically fresh executions of all stages, so prior-round retry failures must not bleed into the new round's budget. Without this, a planning stage that needed retries in round 1 would resume in round 2 at attempt=prior_failed+1.\",\n      \"order\": 3,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Added `request.working_dir.exists()` guard to the spawn ENOENT classification in process_backend.rs:1006. If the working directory doesn't exist, ENOENT comes from the missing cwd, not a missing binary. The failure is classified as TransportFailure (retryable) instead of terminal BinaryNotFound, allowing the retry loop to attempt recovery if the worktree reappears.\",\n      \"order\": 4,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Added 5 unit tests for classify_exit_failure in process_backend.rs #[cfg(test)] module: exit_127_returns_binary_not_found, exit_1_returns_transport_failure, exit_0_returns_transport_failure, signal_killed_returns_transport_failure (SIGSEGV=11), signal_6_returns_transport_failure (SIGABRT=6). Tests use ExitStatus::from_raw() with Unix raw waitpid encoding.\",\n      \"order\": 5,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Added 3 unit tests for derive_resume_state in engine.rs #[cfg(test)] module: resume_after_retryable_failure_preserves_attempt (3 retryable failures → resume at attempt 4), resume_without_prior_failures_starts_at_attempt_1 (no failures → attempt 1), completion_round_advance_resets_retry_tracking (round 1 failures don't carry into round 2).\",\n      \"order\": 6,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Ran cargo fmt to fix formatting differences in test code, verified all checks pass.\",\n      \"order\": 7,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"validation_evidence\": [\n    \"cargo test: 683 passed, 0 failed, 0 ignored (integration tests)\",\n    \"cargo test --lib: 340 passed, 0 failed, 0 ignored (includes 8 new unit tests)\",\n    \"cargo clippy: no warnings or errors\",\n    \"cargo fmt --check: no formatting differences (exit 0)\",\n    \"classify_exit_tests::exit_127_returns_binary_not_found: ExitStatus with exit code 127 maps to BinaryNotFound\",\n    \"classify_exit_tests::exit_1_returns_transport_failure: ExitStatus with exit code 1 maps to TransportFailure\",\n    \"classify_exit_tests::signal_killed_returns_transport_failure: ExitStatus from signal 11 (SIGSEGV) maps to TransportFailure\",\n    \"classify_exit_tests::signal_6_returns_transport_failure: ExitStatus from signal 6 (SIGABRT) maps to TransportFailure\",\n    \"resume_state_tests::resume_after_retryable_failure_preserves_attempt: 3 retryable StageFailed events at attempts 1,2,3 → resume cursor at attempt 4, not 1\",\n    \"resume_state_tests::resume_without_prior_failures_starts_at_attempt_1: no StageFailed events → resume cursor at attempt 1 (default)\",\n    \"resume_state_tests::completion_round_advance_resets_retry_tracking: planning fails at attempts 1,2 in round 1, then succeeds, completion round advances → planning resumes at attempt 1 in round 2 (not 3)\",\n    \"Pre-backoff snapshot write at engine.rs:4643 now uses if-let-Err with tracing::warn, matching the best-effort pattern for non-critical persistence paths\",\n    \"Bare-command ENOENT classification now checks request.working_dir.exists() before classifying as BinaryNotFound — a vanished worktree produces TransportFailure (retryable)\"\n  ]\n}\n```","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"2ab56341-dc03-426c-ace5-dda05f3b0827","total_cost_usd":5.3222569,"usage":{"input_tokens":56,"cache_creation_input_tokens":147439,"cache_read_input_tokens":7461304,"output_tokens":21016,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":147439,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":56,"outputTokens":21016,"cacheReadInputTokens":7461304,"cacheCreationInputTokens":147439,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":5.177825749999999,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":94,"outputTokens":6073,"cacheReadInputTokens":449559,"cacheCreationInputTokens":55213,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.14443114999999998,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"46bbb73a-a0b2-4ed5-852e-d1fc26f9de02"}
